      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`Scalar / object`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><p>{`A resolver can return a single value or an object, as shown in `}<a parentName="td" {...{
                "href": "#defining-a-resolver"
              }}>{`Defining a resolver`}</a>{`. This return value is passed down to any nested resolvers via the `}<code parentName="td" {...{
                "className": "language-text"
              }}>{`parent`}</code>{` argument.`}</p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><code parentName="td" {...{
              "className": "language-text"
            }}>{`Array`}</code></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><p>{`Return an array if and only if your schema indicates that the resolver's associated field contains a list.`}</p><p>{`After you return an array, Apollo Server executes nested resolvers for each item in the array. `}</p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><code parentName="td" {...{
              "className": "language-text"
            }}>{`null`}</code>{` / `}<code parentName="td" {...{
              "className": "language-text"
            }}>{`undefined`}</code></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><p>{`Indicates that the value for the field could not be found.`}</p>{` `}<p>{`If your schema indicates that this resolver's field is nullable, then the operation result has a `}<code parentName="td" {...{
                "className": "language-text"
              }}>{`null`}</code>{` value at the field's position.`}</p><p>{`If this resolver's field is `}<em parentName="td">{`not`}</em>{` nullable, Apollo Server sets the field's `}<em parentName="td">{`parent`}</em>{` to `}<code parentName="td" {...{
                "className": "language-text"
              }}>{`null`}</code>{`. If necessary, this process continues up the resolver chain until it reaches a field that `}<em parentName="td">{`is`}</em>{` nullable. This ensures that a response never includes a `}<code parentName="td" {...{
                "className": "language-text"
              }}>{`null`}</code>{` value for a non-nullable field. When this happens, the response's `}<code parentName="td" {...{
                "className": "language-text"
              }}>{`errors`}</code>{` property will be populated with relevant errors concerning the nullability of that field.`}</p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><a parentName="td" {...{
              "href": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Using_promises"
            }}><code parentName="a" {...{
                "className": "language-text"
              }}>{`Promise`}</code></a></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><p>{`Resolvers often perform asynchronous actions, such as fetching from a database or back-end API. To support this, a resolver can return a promise that resolves to any other supported return type.`}</p></td>
        </tr>
